RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 53. Maiden Claiming Purse 13800. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHE SO COOL rounded the first turn four wide and settled off the pace from the seven eighths pole, closed toward contention three wide into the backstretch, took the lead approaching the seven sixteenths pole and raced clear past the pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and was kept alert through the lane. SOMEBODY LOVES ME saved ground then eased out with a bid into the backstretch, rounded the far turn at the rail, drifted into the lane and settled for second best. MANGORITA settled in the three path early, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and came along for third in later yards. WHY LEA took the lead at the rail approaching the seven eighths pole and rated the pace, was met into the backstretch, gave chase from that point but dropped back toward the three eighths pole and flattened stride while losing ground on the far turn. REGGAETONI steadied early and saved ground, eased outward through the second turn, left the turn outside and showed little response. KOKOLORES settled off the rail and showed little response. RIGHT TO ASSEMBLE stalked from the two and three paths, drew to even terms into the backstretch but faded past the seven sixteenths pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Somebody Loves Me
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,eased out bid 1/2,rail far turn,settled 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Reggaetoni
ENTRY.COMMENT: steadied early,saved ground,eased out 2nd turn,little response

ENTRY.NAME: Mangorita
ENTRY.OWNER: Prostar 10 Stables Inc and The Four Horsemen Racing Stable Inc
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace 3p,bid 7/16,off rail far turn,along 3rd later yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HINK'S PALADIN pressured the pace nearing the seven sixteenths pole and contested the turn at a close disadvantage two deep, dueled for the lead past the eighth pole, raced clear mid-stretch then, just lasted. BALI'S SHADE chased the early pace outside, raced in the three path of the turn, dug in to take second passing the sixteenth pole and just missed. DANCIN IN DUBAI gave chased, rounded the turn in the three and four paths and finished strong to take third the final yards. LION OF THE SEA took the lead nearing the seven sixteenths pole and set a pressured pace, contested the edge nearest the rail on the turn, was caught past the eighth pole and flattened the final sixteenth. BELMULLET gave chase, rounded the turn near the rail then weakened. ASTRAL RIDE chased toward the inside through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. FOREST FROST gave chase inside but weakened at the rail on the turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MANHATTAN WEAVE stumbled at the break but took a quick lead and rated the pace, came under pressure nearing the quarter pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and was steadily handled in the lane. STRINGFELLA rounded the first turn about the four path and left the turn outside, bid leaving the three eighths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn, dueled for second mid-stretch and finished evenly. JOHNNY SWISH was pinched back early, moved to the inside then shut off at the heels of D Tachyon midway on the first turn, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and dug in through the stretch to hold onto third. LET'S GET PHYSICAL raced well off the early pace two deep then eased out and gave chase into the backstretch, rounded the far turn about the five path, dug in from the head of the lane and got up for third at the wire. A FAREWELL YODEL saved ground racing well back, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and ran evenly in the lane. DAKOTA BOY chased the early pace inside then stalked into the first turn, resumed the chase nearing the three eighths pole but flattened off the rail on the far turn. D TACHYON came in and rounded the first turn about the three path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but weakened off the rail on the far turn. OBANNON came in early then steadied between horses past the five eighths pole and never factored.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 13800. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHESAPEAKE CHARLIE settled off the pace about the five path, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and took the lead two deep past the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and was steadily handled in the lane. CAIRO BOOGIE raced well back from early contention, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced two deep on the far turn and cleared second mid-stretch. LIL TOUGHMAN raced with the early pace two deep and took the nod at the nine sixteenths pole, came under pressure nearing the three eighths, but was met past the quarter and weakened leaving the far turn. PLUNK stalked the earlier pace from the three and four paths, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path then flattened in the lane. MASTER THIS raced off the pace in the two and three paths, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. STAVANGER saved ground racing well back, eased out and gave chase into the backstretch, rounded the far turn about the six path and weakened in the lane. CITIZEN'S FIRE set the early pace inside, was met and gave chase from the nine sixteenths pole, but dropped back approaching the three eighths and faded into the far turn. FRONT PORCH saved ground, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but weakened in the five path of the far turn. CHAMPAGNE JAM loped along and was eased the final quarter mile.

ENTRY.NAME: Citizen's Fire
ENTRY.COMMENT: early lead inside,met near 9/16,chased,faded into far turn

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Purse 33900. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCYLOU WHO took the lead nearing the three quarter pole and rated the early pace, was met leaving the nine sixteenths pole and settled close from that point, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths, dueled to recover the lead mid-stretch and drew off the final sixteenth. FLAT DISCOUNT stalked the early pace two deep, took the lead past the nine sixteenths pole and raced clear toward the three eighths, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, was met mid-stretch and relented the final sixteenth. LIKELY CHOICE settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and dueled through the stretch for third. JACK'S LILLY saved ground through the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. CLASSIC COLORS rounded the opening turn in the five path and gave chase from the half mile pole, raced in the three path of the far turn, eased out into the lane but showed little further. MARVELLA NASTY raced in the three path on the first turn, eased out leaving the turn and showed little response through the backstretch. MAP THE MOMENT entered the first turn in the five path and stalked from the nine sixteenths pole, gave chase nearing the three eighths but weakened off the rail on the far turn. ELITE SPEED dwelt at the start and saved ground. FRECCIA D'ARGENTO rated close inside on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole then weakened at the rail on the far turn.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SALSA RITA engaged in close chase through the backstretch, took aim four wide approaching the head of the lane, dug in for the lead later yards and held on. JUSTKISSMYGRITS chased through the backstretch and circled rivals five wide on the turn, was outfinished in the duel through the stretch, got up for second in the final yards and was vanned off. MS HEADLEY set a pressured pace leaving the half mile pole, contested the edge at the rail on the turn, but was met mid-stretch and relented later yards. CHEESE LOUISE chased outside, left the turn widest and finished well. TRUE HEIRESS chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail, lacked room mid-stretch and flattened the final sixteenth. SWEETONTHEGENTS gave chase inside through the backstretch, dropped back approaching the quarter pole, rounded the turn at the rail and ran evenly down the lane. SCARLET TANAGER pressured the pace, contested at a close disadvantage two deep on the turn, then weakened the final sixteenth. LUSCIOUS LOLA gave early chase toward the outside then saved ground on the turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Allowance Purse 35100. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since December 10 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowan ces)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPEAK YOUR MIND gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path, drifted leaving the turn but dug in under steady encouragement to get up the final strides. COLLEGE KID set a pressured pace and contested the edge nearest the rail on the turn, dug in under steady handling leaving the turn but was caught in the final strides and just lasted for second. PRAY FOR THE U S A chased toward the outside, rounded the turn about the four path, angled to the outside leaving the turn, finished well to take third the final yards and just missed second. REIGN ON AND ON chased through the backstretch and contested at a close disadvantage two deep on the turn, but dropped back past the eighth pole and flattened stride late. LADY STORM pressured the pace through the backstretch, but was bumped by Little Bit Of That approaching the quarter pole, rounded the turn near the rail and ran evenly in the lane. CANVAS ART engaged in close early chase but steadied between horses near the three eighths pole, resumed her drive toward the five sixteenths, raced near the rail on the turn, eased out into the lane and showed little more. LITTLE BIT OF THAT pressured the pace inside but was steadied in tight at the rail and bumped Lady Storm approaching the quarter pole, then faded through the turn. SIZZLING HOT was never a factor. GOT YOUR NUMBER gave chase, rounded the turn about the four path, eased out leaving the turn and showed little in the lane. The Stewards reviewed, then dismissed, a claim of foul against the rider of College Kid for alleged interference nearing the quarter pole, lodged by the rider of Lady Storm.

ENTRY.NAME: Canvas Art
ENTRY.COMMENT: close early chase,steadied near 3/8,chased,rail turn,empty lane

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased outside,4p turn,angled out 1/8,finished well,just miss 2nd

ENTRY.OWNER: Devane William E and King Adam

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAPIT TO THE WIRE stalked off the rail on the first turn, pulled himself to the lead nearing the seven sixteenths pole and was urged clear toward the three eighths, widened at the rail on the far turn then steadily handled through the lane. ITS OVER settled in the two and three paths the first turn then eased out into the backstretch, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced two deep on the far turn and ran evenly to late stretch before flattening stride. SULEMAN saved ground well off the pace, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and finished evenly to take third under the wire. BOOK OF DELANCEY rounded the first turn in the three path, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. GOT FLOFFY rated close inside on the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail but flattened inside the eighth pole. URBAN WARRIOR stalked the pace inside on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but faded past the five sixteenths. LUNAR IMAGE raced well off the pace about the three path on the opening turn, showed little response through the backstretch and ran in the three path of the far turn. PROUD UNION was shuffled back shortly after the start and was not a factor. CAPTAIN CARDO took the lead at the three quarter pole and rated a short lead, but was caught at the seven sixteenths pole and faded toward the far turn. RUNNING VIOLENCE stalked the early pace from the four path, gave chase into the backstretch but faded past the three eighths pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Got Floffy
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,chased 7/16,rail far turn,flattened lane

ENTRY.NAME: Tapit to the Wire
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,up near 7/16,clear near 3/8,rail,steady urging
